<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-06T23:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-06T23:30:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AB/9–751: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in India</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Henderson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-07T10:00:00+05:30">September 7, 1951—10 a. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>874. Took occasion this morning express view Graham as suggested last
                                para <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 524 Sept 6. He
                                replied he had given matter careful consideration. Fact was however
                                he had already recd informally from both govts replies to points and
                                suggestions contained in document to be presented to them today. He
                                did not believe therefore it wld serve any useful purpose him stay
                                on merely in order receive formal document setting forth what had
                                already been given him informally. He convinced time has come for
                                him leave <gloss target="#t_SOA1">SOA</gloss> and is therefore going
                                on with plans set forth <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>
                                871 Sept 6.</p>
                            <p>Rptd info Karachi 57.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Henderson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>